(5, 1, '2017-06-21 10:09:08', '2017-06-21 10:09:08', '<em style=\"color: #757575; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 300; text-align: justify;\">We (Luana, Johnathan, Marilena, Sarah and Willow) went to Brussels for the One World Documentary film festival organised by a school called Atheneum Brussels. In the 5 days, we watched 5 documentaries about human rights and had a panel with experts for each topic afterwards. On Monday we watched the War Show about the Syrian war; On Tuesday we watched Plastic China about pollution; On Wednesday we watched Prison Sisters about Afghan women’s rights; On Thursday we watched the Opposition about civilians being forced to leave home in New Papua Guinea; On Friday we watched the Pearl of Africa about a transgender’s story in Uganda. The overall experience was great in terms of the movies and the connection we’ve made with the local school and host families.</em>', 'One World Documentary Film Festival Brussels', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'april16-one-world-documentary-film-festival-brussels__trashed', '', '', '2017-06-23 09:04:57', '2017-06-23 09:04:57', '', 0, 'http://localhost/project_week/?p=5', 0, 'post', '', 0),
