(13, 1, '2017-06-21 10:20:48', '2017-06-21 10:20:48', 'Our project week group consist of Arabi, Martha, Marion, Alejo, Tereza, Sydney, Zaafir, Jeremiah, Yi Wynn, and Abdul. We conducted this project week based on the idea from Tereza a native of the Czech Republic. The Kangaroo Orphanage is a halfway house of sorts where children are placed until they either are moved to a permanent long term orphanage or the court awards a guardian custody. The House was a somewhat beautiful light in something that when you pause and think is a very sad situation. With Tereza as our Guide, we undertook a variety of challenges and learning objectives. The ones we followed were:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Design and pursue a student-led project.</li>\r\n 	<li>Provide a service to an organization/community.</li>\r\n 	<li>Organize activities outside the campus.</li>\r\n 	<li>Explore a new country and culture.</li>\r\n 	<li>Improve your organisation, communication and collaboration skills.</li>\r\n 	<li>Get to know more about yourself and your group.</li>\r\n 	<li>Achieve a positive (social) change.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe achieved the first goal of designing and pursuing a student-led project. By planning this project we fulfil this first goal. With Tereza, a native of Prague,  at the helm of the designing the project we arranged times and dates to go to the orphanage along with how to get from our Airbnb to the orphanage which was out of walking distance, to say the least being two metro changes and two buses away. We pre-arrange our service activities at the orphanage where needed and they requested that we play  with the young kids and paint in the morning and the entire group playing games and telling the older children, now returned from school, about our countries.', 'Prague Orphanage', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', '13__trashed', '', '', '2017-06-23 09:04:47', '2017-06-23 09:04:47', '', 0, 'http://localhost/project_week/?p=13', 0, 'post', '', 0),
