(584, 1, '2016-06-27 06:59:23', '2016-06-27 06:59:23', 'During the June Project Week our team has been working on the Refugee welcome guide. The Guide has been created in order to help the refugees in finding the cheapest places in town. The first day we met two women from the refugee camp, where they shared with us their first experiences and how difficult it has been for them to find their way in shops with affordable prices.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-585 size-large\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/13499801_10209795966801884_753748227_o-768x1024.jpg\" alt=\"13499801_10209795966801884_753748227_o\" width=\"700\" height=\"933\" />\n\nWe understood that there was a genuine need for our project when one of the women told us that she had been starving for two days in a raw because she was not able to guide herself in the city. With the guidance of our supervisors we created some forms that consisted of the goods that the refugees need. We included the prices and the description of the goods and also detailed directions of how to reach the shop from the refugee center. After that, we visited the shops and filled in the forms. We managed to collect a significantly big amount of data that will be included in the guide.Finally we met a group of university students that introduced us to their initiative web platform where refuges can find guidance in many areas such as healthcare and shopping.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-586 size-large\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/13509764_10209795966961888_1434780437_o-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"13509764_10209795966961888_1434780437_o\" width=\"700\" height=\"525\" />\n\nThey invited us to upload the information that we have collected in the area of shopping so that more refugees have access into it. Although the project did not work as we expected due to some complications in communication and organization inside our group and with our contacts, we discovered in which areas we should improve and now we all feel more prepared and experienced for our next project. Our project is strongly interrelated with the UWC values and missions as each member of the group experienced a personal challenge, there was celebration of difference and intercultural understanding and we tried to be as environmentally sustainable as possible.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-587 size-large\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/image1-1-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"image1 (1)\" width=\"700\" height=\"525\" />\n\n-By Sofia Iris Kormpaki, Veronica Bejm Franco, Mesut Caliskan, Jacob Elton, Len Tha Lang, Dechen Zangmo, Cami Lindo, Oumaima Rhalem', 'Refugee welcome guide', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'june16-refugee-welcome-guide', '', '', '2017-06-23 10:05:56', '2017-06-23 10:05:56', '', 0, 'http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/?p=584', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(589, 1, '2016-06-27 11:46:39', '2016-06-27 11:46:39', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Our Project Week was to continue with the idea of the Student Handbook that was started last year by two past students. Last year this handbook was really helpful for new students to have all the most important information in one place, although there were some flaws in the book. So our idea was to create another Student Handbook in a new format that will be applicable for all students with different levels of English. Also another problem that we have discovered with the previous handbook was that it was given only to the residential students, leaving day students with no information. That’s why in our booklet we covered topics that are related to residential students but also some for day students, so they will also find this handbook useful next year.</span>\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-590 size-full\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/student-booklet.png\" alt=\"student booklet\" width=\"782\" height=\"438\" />\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">During this four days we managed to create new Student Handbook. We divided work between the four of us, so each person was responsible for different part of the student handbook. Before we started writing we did a little research to see what other students thought about the last years handbook, what was good and what would that change. Based on that we did an outline of our student handbook and then we were just writing. We met regularly to check each other progress and finally put everything we got together to create a completely new Student Handbook.\nOur Project Week for sure relates to the UWC value <b>Compassion and Service, because we created something for our school that hopefully will be useful next year for new students.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">by Jeremiah, Clara, Wiktoria &amp; Michalina</span>', 'Student Handbook', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'june16-student-handbook', '', '', '2017-06-23 10:05:12', '2017-06-23 10:05:12', '', 0, 'http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/?p=589', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(592, 1, '2016-06-27 11:51:59', '2016-06-27 11:51:59', 'It all started with takecarebnb, an organization based in Amsterdam that helped refugees to find local host families. We were all excited to work with them until we found out one day before that there had been a huge miscommunication with them since the early start of the collaboration with them. We were all worried about what was going on. Since it was very late we did not have many options to choose from so the only option possible was the animal farm. Some of us were not so enthusiastic because of the fear of being around animals, however we were determined to accomplish the project week so we undertook the challenge.\n\n<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/animal-farm.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-593\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-593 size-full\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/animal-farm.png\" alt=\"animal farm\" width=\"601\" height=\"359\" /></a>\n\nThe first day was quite hard physical work cutting tree branches and transporting them and by the end of the day we were all very tired. Also we realized that we needed to communicate more effectively with the owners and workers in the farm when we wanted to share our feelings about a certain task given to us. On the second day the temperatures were quite high and for some of us that were fasting this proved to be very challenging. The task on the second day was cutting grass and cleaning the goat barn and the inside of the main facility. By the third day all of us got more used to the kind of work done in the farm so for all of us it felt easier. It is certain that for all the of us it was not the most enjoyable way we could have spent three days and not the ideal project week but there was need for that work to be done and we did learn a lot throughout the process. We learned about efficient communication, how to work better as a group, punctuality, perseverance.\n\nby Gisela, Sophie, Holly, Helen, Nina, Nelson and Omnia', 'Takecarebnb --> Kinderboerderij De Heeg', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '592', '', '', '2017-06-23 10:05:04', '2017-06-23 10:05:04', '', 0, 'http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/?p=592', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(598, 1, '2016-06-28 06:10:44', '2016-06-28 06:10:44', '<div>~~</div>\n<div>In our project week we worked on the planning of the 2016 introduction week for the new DP1s. This includes planning activities and events, establishing clear communication with staff members and tutors and making student participation the best it can be. Yet our main aim was to make sure everyone has a chance to participate and feel welcome. Having members from both the day and residential community, we were able to get different inputs in the planning so that it suits as many people as possible. Even though last year there was also an introduction week team, not as a project week though, there were multiple aspects and events that could have been organised and communicated better, which is what we worked hard on changing. There was a genuine need for this project week as the time given for us to work in a team resulted in what we believe will be a successful and fun first two weeks of school, which will hopefully show the new DP1s the welcoming atmosphere UWCM has to offer as well as connect DP1 and DP2 as well as day and residential students. We really enjoyed working together and we are ready for our new firsties!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>by Japhlet, Juul, Dominique, Valeria, Lotte, Melih, Aya, Ane, Akke and Tamar - Intro Week Team</div>', 'Introduction week Prep team', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'june16-introduction-week-prep-team', '', '', '2017-06-23 10:04:56', '2017-06-23 10:04:56', '', 0, 'http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/?p=598', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(600, 1, '2016-06-28 06:16:16', '2016-06-28 06:16:16', 'For the past 4 days, our group had an intensive yet super fun time learning different writing techniques to help people next year.\r\n\r\nTo be honest, at first I doubted my abilities in writing. Coming to UWC and taking up IB was challenging for me in terms of having so many essay-based subjects. Yet after workshops with Larissa and Johannes, I realize I am very privileged to be able to speak English fluently and convey my intended message with ease. This project week is basically preparing us to set up a writing support team.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-627\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/File_001.jpeg\" alt=\"File_001\" width=\"3264\" height=\"2448\">\r\n\r\nWhy did this all start? Well, in our community, we have quite diverse English levels. We have a very wide range of English speakers, ranging from native speakers to people who have never spoken a word of English until 1 month before they come. Since at UWCM, we do the IB in English. From what we see from our friends and peers to our very personal experience, we feel that there is not enough support for writing in general, especially when IB is such an ‘essay based’ curriculum. Hopefully, after this intensive kind of short course, we can establish a writing support team to help students with any kind of problem with writing in any subjects.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-628\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/File_006.jpeg\" alt=\"File_006\" width=\"3264\" height=\"2448\">\r\n\r\nThroughout the course of the project week, I myself took a lot away from what Larissa and Johannes presented. Larissa focussed on the technical parts for writing an essay especially for English A students, while Johannes highlighted the needs of students who take English acquisition. In order for the support group to work, we really have to cater for needs of different individuals, exploring the differences between a native speaker and a non-native and how to approach them were particularly useful. It is also very important to be empathetic. We’ve all been through different struggles on our road of learning, we want them to feel safe and positive when coming to us, it id only by them feeling safe to share their work then we can all learn and improve.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-629\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/File_008-1024x768.jpeg\" alt=\"File_008\" width=\"700\" height=\"525\">\r\n\r\nAll in all, it was a very fruitful and intensive project week. I hope we could all make the writing support a reality next year!\r\n\r\nIt will be all WRITE!\r\n\r\nWritten by Melody Lam.', 'Writing support group', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'june16-writing-support-group', '', '', '2017-06-23 10:04:46', '2017-06-23 10:04:46', '', 0, 'http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/?p=600', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(602, 1, '2016-06-28 06:23:49', '2016-06-28 06:23:49', 'During our project we spend our time repairing the residential/school bicycles. This would benefit the school community due to the fact that students arriving next school year for DP1 will have transport to for example the city of Maastricht. This will also benefit the soon to be DP2’s because over the course of the year they might have run in to some problems with their bicycle which we repaired so that they can also have a fresh start at the beginning of the next school year, Transport wise. What we’ve accomplished during this project week is that we tried our at most to repair the damaged/nonworking bicycles. This means: Replacing the inner tube, gluing the inner tube, oiling the chain + breaks, filling up the tires, reattaching breaks, wheels, locks, fenders etc. As we are not bicycle experts we lacked some knowledge thus the fact being we were also giving a limited amount of tools and funding to fully repair the residential bicycle. For example on some bicycles the wheel was bend which means that the bicycle did not function. We would have to purchase an entire new wheel in order to fix this problem. A very common issue we ran into was that more then 1/3 of the bicycles had missing keys meaning that the level of repairing on those specific bicycles was very limited. We could only tire pressure and if all the parts were firm.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-603 size-full\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/bike1.png\" alt=\"bike1\" width=\"712\" height=\"283\">\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/bike2.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-604\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-604 size-full\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/bike2.png\" alt=\"bike2\" width=\"708\" height=\"311\"></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/bike3.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-605\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-605 size-full\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/bike3.png\" alt=\"bike3\" width=\"714\" height=\"311\"></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/bike4.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-606\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-606 size-full\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/bike4.png\" alt=\"bike4\" width=\"711\" height=\"312\"></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/bike5.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-607\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-607 size-full\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/bike5.png\" alt=\"bike5\" width=\"710\" height=\"312\"></a>\r\n\r\nOverall it was a good experience and our project has shown a clear link between the mission and the values of UWC. By creating safer and better transport for the students we also created more learning opportunities. Also by improving the school owned bicycles we can promote the use of this way of environmentally friendly transport. Everyone got along and got treated with patience and respect. Therefore we learned to cooperate with each other. It was of course also a personal challenge for everyone on the team because not everyone was as well known with bicycles as the other. In conclusion taking the lack of tools and other items such as keys and spare parts into consideration it was quite successful.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBy Tristan', 'Bike repair group', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'june16-bike-repair-group', '', '', '2017-06-23 10:02:15', '2017-06-23 10:02:15', '', 0, 'http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/?p=602', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(611, 1, '2016-06-28 11:21:12', '2016-06-28 11:21:12', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Maastricht is only 50km away from the nuclear reactor Tihange located in Belgium. Pressurized water reactors such as Tihange are built to have a lifespan of 30 to 40 years, which means that Tihange should have been shut down in 2012. This however did not happen, its lifespan was even extended to 2025. When there is a serious problem or some kind of damage, the reactor shuts down automatically. Over the past two year it has happened hundreds of times and every single time the Belgian government has re-started it &nbsp;manually. If there is a core meltdown accident, we could face similar consequences as we have experienced with Chernobyl and Fukushima. Carolin and I found that no one in school is informed about this local issue and decided that we want to raise awareness. Our aim is to inform people in order to avoid panic if something should happen, since that would create a disastrous chaos. &nbsp;We have created power point presentation and will be printing leaflets that we want to share with the school community next school year. This will give people a detailed overview of &nbsp;what exactly the issue is, what they should prepare for and how to act in a worst case scenario. We will offer people to come talk to us if they should have any further concerns or are unsure. </span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/tih1.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-612\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-612\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/tih1.png\" alt=\"tih1\" width=\"769\" height=\"575\"></a> <a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/tih2.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-613\"><img class=\"wp-image-613 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/tih2.png\" alt=\"tih2\" width=\"742\" height=\"491\"></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/tih4.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-615\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-615 size-full\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/tih4.png\" alt=\"tih4\" width=\"451\" height=\"602\"></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOur PW links to the UWC mission and values in several ways. The UWC mission states “UWC makes education a force to unite people, nations and cultures for peace and <b>a sustainable future</b>”. Sustainability plays a major role in this project, since we have to invest in sustainable energy resources rather than for example nuclear energy, that carries too many risks when not operated correctly. Looking at the nine values, a few stand out: “Mutual responsibility and respect”, “Respect for the environment” and ”Action and personal example”. These apply to our PW as it is our mutual responsibility to consider and act upon these issues as it can only be resolved when people work together and find solutions. Respect for the environment it very obvious as the environment would majorly suffer under a core meltdown. Action is needed in the resolution of this issue and Carolin and I have taken part in the demonstration (personal example) and are planning on signing the petition &nbsp;(min. Age 18). Thus, all three values apply.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-614 size-full\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/tih3.png\" alt=\"tih3\" width=\"743\" height=\"563\">', 'The nuclear reactor Tihange in Belgium', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'june16-the-nuclear-reactor-tihange-in-belgium', '', '', '2017-06-23 10:02:01', '2017-06-23 10:02:01', '', 0, 'http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/?p=611', 0, 'post', '', 0);
