(760, 1, '2017-06-23 08:59:20', '2017-06-23 08:59:20', 'On 4th November, Vincent Frenken visited us to present a map of Maastricht and neighbouring communities in terms of social challenges faced especially by youth.\n\nVincent has worked for many years for Trayekt, the equivalent of the Social Services in NL, and he works mostly at night with youth in the streets: \"lover boys\", female prostitution, etc.\n\nThis was a shocking presentation for many of us since we were not aware of the dimension of these problems.\n\nThere\'s also a street culture by which some youth make up big stories of what they have done that aren´t always true.\n\nBesides these issues, one of the biggest problems among youngsters and young families or single-headed-households in Maastricht is the level of indebtedness, which at times makes these people resort to illegal and/or criminal activities to make quick money.\n\n&nbsp;', 'Trayekt - Vincent Frenken', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '497-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-23 08:59:20', '2017-06-23 08:59:20', '', 497, 'http://localhost/project_week/2017/06/23/497-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(761, 1, '2017-06-23 08:59:38', '2017-06-23 08:59:38', '<u>Integrated activities and projects with local industry 2015-2016</u>\nThis is a programme initiated by the Province of Limburg with the goal of making connections between the provincial government, educational institutions in the province and the local industry. Students from UWC Maastricht joined two regional vocational schools to work on two case studies developed by two local companies.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nUWC Maastricht students were matched with the following two companies:\n\n1.Smurfit Kappa (Roermond)\nSmurfit Kappa is one of the world leading providers of paper-based packaging (44.000 employees worldwide). Together with the Cita Verde College in Roermond and Leeuwenborgh in Sittard, our students worked on a project where they depicted the actual working of circular economy for Smurfit Kappa. Students were asked to think of a purpose for some of the waste materials from Smurfit Kappa. How can they be developed into a product? Our students followed the process of research, lab work and design and presented that as part of their broader case study of how circular economy works in practice. They developed a sort of marketing of Smurfit Kappa’s sustainability management and <u>won the competition</u>.\n\n2. Arion (Geleen)\nA company producing innovative solutions for the healthcare market. Examples of their products are aids to pull on and off compression stockings and products that allow washing patients without water. Especially the last product group, the washing without water products, is growing enormously in the last couple of years. They therefore developed a research question for students to focus on.\n<em>“How can Arion make use of cultural, anthropological, philosophical, and historical findings on washing in general in the countries where it is currently active (NL, BE, DE, DK, ES) and is going to be active (UK, FR, SE)?”</em>\nThe goals of the activity were:\n\n- To provide students with an insight into the daily running of a business.\n\n- To allow students to independently work on a real life case study.\n-  For students to explore how innovation can be a force of positive change.\n- To create a network between our school, other schools, businesses and the local\n\ngovernment.\nUWC Maastricht will continue its participation in the project next academic year.\n\n<strong><em> </em></strong>\n\n<strong><em> </em></strong>', 'Limburg & Co. Project', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '507-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-23 08:59:38', '2017-06-23 08:59:38', '', 507, 'http://localhost/project_week/2017/06/23/507-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(762, 1, '2017-06-23 08:59:46', '2017-06-23 08:59:46', 'On 21st October Michal Steyn, chairman and one of the founders of <a href=\"http://stcmaastricht.nl/en/\">ServetheCity Maastricht</a> (STC), visited us during our YSE session to help us understand our host city better and make us think about our attitudes and actions towards our new community.\n\nThis software engineer from South Africa had earlier in his professional life joined a group of friends with their startup technology company iKubu, which eventually invested a micro radar system and was later acquired by an American company.\n\nMichal moved to the USA in 2014, where he started his current software consultancy business. In 2015 he relocated with his family to Maastricht, where he divides his time between engineering and STC.\n\nThese are some of Michal\'s inspiring lines:\n\n<em>\"What if we got to know the members of our community by name and not by numbers and needs?</em>\n\n<em>Each community has something to give and something to receive. Don\'t pity them, have compassion!</em>\n\n<em>There are needs even in this room, walk around with new eyes, be aware of the problems around you.</em>\n\n<em>Starting a business must be one of the most humanitarian actions you can do: feeding a family is entrepreneurship.</em>\n\n<em>Keep in mind always the triple bottom line: social equity, economic, and environmental factors =&gt; PEOPLE, PLANET &amp; PROFIT.</em>\n\n<em>Be playful and dream again, don´t let education ruin your creativity.\"</em>\n\nMichal also talked about their current projects with the Refugee Centre in Maastricht.', 'Serve The City Maastricht - Michal Steyn', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '495-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-23 08:59:46', '2017-06-23 08:59:46', '', 495, 'http://localhost/project_week/2017/06/23/495-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(763, 1, '2017-06-23 09:00:00', '2017-06-23 09:00:00', 'On Monday 23rd November, Bert Jongen - a senior member of the local government, long-life advocate for the rights of people with disabilities and an expert in Social Entrepreneurship in the Limburg region - joined DP2 students for a chat within the UWCM YSE Hub.\n\nBert is the author of ‘<em>Werken met Passie. </em><em>SociaalOndernemen in the Praktijk</em>and’, a book about those entrepreneurs working with passion in the Netherlands and the main social enterprises in this country.\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/IMG_0639.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-503\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-503\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/IMG_0639-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_0639\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a></p>\nStudents refreshed their ideas about the key features of a social enterprise and learnt about social enterprises in the Limburg region.\n\n<em>\"A social enterprise must fulfill the 3Ps: People, Planet and Profit. Profit is not their goal but a tool to enable their social project, to make it sustainable. The money is used to cover the costs of the project.\"</em>\n\n\"A social enterprise is a way to work within the capitalist system to find solutions to problems. [...] It\'s about the intention behind the \'helping\'...people and disabilities or other\".\n\nThere\'s now specific law in NL and a certification for social enterprises.\n\nThere are 25 firms in NL specialised in employment opportunities for people with disabilities as there are only 1 in 4 chances of finding a job as a person with disability in NL.\n\nCrowdfunding donors are a good idea to start financing your project, at least to cover costs.\n\nThe examples of Ben&amp;Jerry ice-cream and StreetwiZe were discussed by the group.\n\nBert highlighted the following as the main social problems in Maastricht at the moment:\n<ul>\n	<li>Unemployment</li>\n	<li>Solitude of elderly people (above 50 yeas old)</li>\n	<li>Youth with severe debt (several thousand euros)</li>\n</ul>\nThere are no social enterprises at the municipal level but the local goverment sponsors 140 social organisations. For example, Trajekt receives 12 million euros per year to run projects.\n\nBert mentioned the big niche for UWC Maastricht students starting social entrepreneurial projects and pointed at the potential of a project to awaken the province about funds to help young people start social enterprises.\n\n&nbsp;', 'Bert Jongen: \"Working with Passion\"', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '502-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-23 09:00:00', '2017-06-23 09:00:00', '', 502, 'http://localhost/project_week/2017/06/23/502-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(764, 1, '2017-06-23 09:00:06', '2017-06-23 09:00:06', 'The weekend of 28th and 29th November, 20 students from the YSE programme (DP1 students)  and the UWCM YSE Hub (DP2 students) attended the event MYB Maastricht. A start-up weekend full of workshops, inspirational sessions, legal advice, business models, social entrepreneurship, networking, coaching and pitching.\n\nAn action-oriented event that offered participants a unique occasion to channel their creativity and talents. Hosted by Smile to the Future Foundation. Sponsored by Gemeente Maastricht, Maastricht University, Stichting Elisabeth Strouven and CODE043.\n\nOur students constituted most of the attendees of this event. They can be seen in these photos and videos below:\n\n<a href=\"http://mindyourbusinessmaastricht.com/\">http://mindyourbusinessmaastricht.com/</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://smiletothefuture.org/mind-your-business-exceeds-expectations/\">http://smiletothefuture.org/mind-your-business-exceeds-expectations/</a>\n\n&nbsp;', 'Mind Your Business Maastricht', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '505-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-23 09:00:06', '2017-06-23 09:00:06', '', 505, 'http://localhost/project_week/2017/06/23/505-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(765, 1, '2017-06-23 09:01:54', '2017-06-23 09:01:54', 'Three of our sessions have been dedicated to understanding better the concept of Human Rights.\n\nLast 2nd December, three members of the UWCM Amnesty International group joined us to present the 16 Days of Activism for the Elimination of Violence Against Women and Girls.\n\nThe three DP1 students (Mathilde Barland, Nusret Yildirim and Emi Lee Ai Yen) talked about AI\'s efforts wordwide and then proposed and interactive activity for the MYP5 students.\n\n<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/AI-members-presentation1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-253\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/AI-members-presentation1-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"AI members presentation\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> <a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/getting-ready-for-a-game2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-257\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/getting-ready-for-a-game2-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"getting ready for a game\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\n<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Playing1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-255\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Playing1-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Playing\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> <a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Reflections1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-256\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Reflections1-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Reflections\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>\n\nStudents picked different roles of a variety of individuals in many different countries and situations and they had to answer to several statements in relation to how much their rights were being fulfilled or not. A very interesting exercise which made us think outside the box and reflect once again about how privileged we are for the comforts we have...', 'Human Rights', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '198-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-23 09:01:54', '2017-06-23 09:01:54', '', 198, 'http://localhost/project_week/2017/06/23/198-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(766, 1, '2017-06-23 09:02:06', '2017-06-23 09:02:06', 'UWC Maastricht decided to embark in the Serious Request of the Red Cross this year to raise awareness about the challenges to the Right of Education of thousands of children and youth around the world who are also experiencing war or conflict in their countries.\n\nThis was an excellent opportunity as well for MYP5 students to design their own actions to fundraise for the Red Cross and other MYP students and staff also came up with their own ideas to raise awareness while having fun: <a href=\"https://kominactie.3fm.nl/actie/united-world-college-maastricht-komt-in-actie\">UWC Maastricht with Serious Request 2015</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Lockdown-preps.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-244\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Lockdown-preps-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Lockdown preps\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> <a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Serious-request-preps.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-246\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Serious-request-preps-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Serious request preps\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>\n\n<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Sponge-posters.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-245\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Sponge-posters-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Sponge posters\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>\n\nTheir learning outcomes have been that working as a team is not always easy because self-management requires planning and effort, that lower number of members in the team help to manage it better, that internal communication is something important which needs to be taken seriously to inform all aspects of the process and finally, that the will and commitment to a project is more than 50% of the success of that project.\n\n&nbsp;', 'Serious Request 2015 - Supporting the Red Cross for the Right to Education of children and youth in conflict areas', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '195-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-23 09:02:06', '2017-06-23 09:02:06', '', 195, 'http://localhost/project_week/2017/06/23/195-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(767, 1, '2017-06-23 09:03:22', '2017-06-23 09:03:22', 'On 9th November, eight MYP5 students were invited by the Kids Rights Foundation and UWC Nederland to attend the <a href=\"http://childrenpeaceprize.org\" target=\"_blank\">Children\'s Peace Prize</a> awarding ceremony in The Hague.\n\nThese students were selected owing to their great presentations about the Sustainable Development Goals to different audiences within the Active Global Citizenship Programme.\n\n<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/IMG-20151110-WA0000.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-188\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/IMG-20151110-WA0000-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"IMG-20151110-WA0000\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a> <a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/IMG_20151109_134257182.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-189\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/IMG_20151109_134257182-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20151109_134257182\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a> <a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/IMG_20151109_135336856.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-192\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/IMG_20151109_135336856-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20151109_135336856\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a> <a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/IMG_20151109_153040902.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-200\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/IMG_20151109_135030157-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20151109_135030157\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a>\n\nIt was a privilege to listen to Liberian Nobel Peace Laureate 2011, Leymah Gbowee, handing in the prize to 17 year old Abraham Keita: \"Is this the world we want our children to learn from? [...] Can we all make a commitment today to live lives that <span class=\"il\">kids</span> will be proud to emulate?                                         STEP OUT AND DO ONE GOOD THING EVERYDAY THAT EVERYONE ELSE IS SCARED TO DO!\"\n\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-191\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/IMG_20151109_153040902-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20151109_153040902\" width=\"382\" height=\"215\" />\n\nOur students were very inspired by the life example, leadership, passion and public speaking skills of the 2015 Children\'s Peace Prize Winner Abraham Keita (17 years old). He comes from the West Point slum in Liberia and is a human <span class=\"il\">rights</span> campaigner against police brutality and violence against women, girls and youth in general.\n\n<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/IMG_20151109_164716234.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-193\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/IMG_20151109_164716234-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20151109_164716234\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a>\n\nA memorable evening!\n\n&nbsp;', 'Children\'s Peace Prize in The Hague', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '187-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-23 09:03:22', '2017-06-23 09:03:22', '', 187, 'http://localhost/project_week/2017/06/23/187-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(768, 1, '2017-06-23 09:06:05', '2017-06-23 09:06:05', 'Last Friday, 11<sup>th</sup> December, my friend Praise and I attended an event in Leiden, the Netherlands.   The event was organized by <a href=\"http://www.defenceforchildren.org/\">Defense for Children</a> and we got to meet Abraham Keita who won the <a href=\"http://www.childrenspeaceprize.org/\">Children’s Peace Prize</a> in November 2015.  Abraham Keita is an amazing youngster from Liberia who has done countless things to help his and others’ communities.  He is also an inspiring person who believes that children have the right to do what they believe is best for them.  When he was 9 years old he heard a story of a random girl who was raped, tortured, and killed.  The story made him realize that this time it happened to a girl whom he did not know at all but it could soon happen to his friends, cousins, and sisters if this issue was not stopped.  This whole incident inspired him to start a campaign against this problem and there were 500 children who joined him.  As a child he was always very passionate and he believes that everyone (especially children) can make a difference in the world.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_203\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/defence-for-children.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-203\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/defence-for-children-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"Defense for Children\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a> Defense for Children[/caption]\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-204\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/12314024_919013428178826_8788796030910595427_n-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"12314024_919013428178826_8788796030910595427_n\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /> <a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/abraham-keita.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-205\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/abraham-keita-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"abraham keita\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\nI had some really inspiring moments talking to some young university students who were social entrepreneurs with extreme passion to help others and to work towards their dreams.  Most of them are quite young but they all work really hard hoping to change and make the world a better place. They are people who see problems in their society as something that needs to be solved and they take initiative to show the world what they want to happen.  This really inspires me to live my life fully and to serve others with what I have. It also shows me that if these people can make a difference in life, so can I.\n\nI realized that somehow some of us don’t think our YSE class is useful but I come to really appreciate what it has taught me and how important it is to everyone and the society we live in.  I am really grateful to have this opportunity to remind myself of what I have taken for granted.\n\n<em>Ahai Vang (Laos)</em>', 'A dialogue with Abraham Keita - Children´s Peace Prize laureate 2015', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '202-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-23 09:06:05', '2017-06-23 09:06:05', '', 202, 'http://localhost/project_week/2017/06/23/202-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(769, 1, '2017-06-23 09:07:47', '2017-06-23 09:07:47', '<div><em>We (Luana, Johnathan, Marilena, Sarah and Willow) went to Brussels for the One World Documentary film festival organised by a school called Atheneum Brussels. In the 5 days, we watched 5 documentaries about human rights and had a panel with experts for each topic afterwards. On Monday we watched the War Show about the Syrian war; On Tuesday we watched Plastic China about pollution; On Wednesday we watched Prison Sisters about Afghan women\'s rights; On Thursday we watched the Opposition about civilians being forced to leave home in New Papua Guinea; On Friday we watched the Pearl of Africa about a transgender’s story in Uganda. The overall experience was great in terms of the movies and the connection we’ve made with the local school and host families.</em></div>', 'One World Documentary Film Festival Brussels', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '756-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-23 09:07:47', '2017-06-23 09:07:47', '', 756, 'http://localhost/project_week/2017/06/23/756-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
