(778, 1, '2017-06-23 09:14:56', '2017-06-23 09:14:56', 'This year a group of 5 students did a project at an organization called CNME. It is called Centrum voor Natuur en Milieu Educatie which is a place to learn about nature, environmental education and apply it to real life in Maastricht. The CNME is a group that makes Maastricht beautiful again and makes more safer spaces for endangered species such as the slow worm and podarcis muralis (a reptile that lives on stones).\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/lizard.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-690\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-690\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/lizard.png\" alt=\"lizard\" width=\"612\" height=\"413\"></a>\r\n\r\nDuring the project week we worked in the North-West area of Maastricht. We worked in closed and open areas. On top of the roof and on the ground. Some days it was boiling heat and others were not too bad.\r\nOn the first day we went to Fort Willem and cutted grass on top of a roof. This took the whole day because there was a lot of grass. It was a nice day to scrap all the grass and to throw it of the roof in the truck. We were all hard at work, cleaning it that grass was nice and smooth.\r\nThe second was the hardest of them all, not of work but of the weather. It was soo hot that we had take a lot more breaks than we expected but we got a lot of work done too.\r\nThe best moment was to walk in the tunnels because it was very nice and chilly in there.\r\nThe third day was cutting away the “Japanese knotweed” away because there are no animals that live underneath it and it is extremely invasive. So we had to make sure that it wouldn’t grow on different spots which made us dig to the root of those plants.\r\nThe last day was a nice way of finishing our project week, we had to clean stone and grass so when it does get hot outside, the podarcis muralis can warm faster because of the stones absorbing heat faster.\r\nAfter this project all of us felt that we had made difference to the Maastricht community and we hope next there will be a group going to the CNME to get the same experience as we did\r\nThank you CNME,\r\n\r\nChristian, Leander, Joel, Joey &amp; Ronald', 'CNME', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '689-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-23 09:14:56', '2017-06-23 09:14:56', '', 689, 'http://localhost/project_week/2017/06/23/689-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(779, 1, '2017-06-23 09:15:21', '2017-06-23 09:15:21', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">UWCM has many places for people to spend time together, from the common rooms to people’s own individual rooms. For events the school can be considered a nice meeting spot, offering places for both conferences and meetings. However, a nice area that offers everyone a place to just really chill and relax was not present on campus the way it should. </span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-671\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/furniture2.png\" alt=\"furniture2\" width=\"692\" height=\"190\">\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Our PW decided to face that issue and work on the mensa. We saw an opportunity to create something for everyone on campus to enjoy for a long time to come. We decided to use wooden pallets to create some extra furniture for mensa as well as redecorate it. On day three we had accomplished a lot. We had made two couches, and one table which we also painted. We got three rugs to add to the decoration and two closets, one of which we painted. Another couch that can be turned into a bed was donated to us and we constructed it and added it to the mensa. We added the lanterns from the graduation to make it even better looking. </span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-672\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/furniture3.png\" alt=\"furniture3\" width=\"502\" height=\"369\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The place looks a much more nice, and our hard work made the mensa chill area look much better. Our work paid off as it is already more inhabited. Of course we linked our project week to the UWC values as well. All of us had&nbsp;<strong>personal challenge</strong> as we set out to create a better mensa. We learned about construction and challenged ourselves in order to make our project as good as possible.&nbsp;<strong>Respect for the environment</strong> is yet another value we upheld. We recycled wooden pallets and reused old material in order to make the mensa look as nice as we could. Instead of buying new furniture, we went to the second hand store and reused old furniture as well.\r\n<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/furniture.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-670\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-670\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/furniture.png\" alt=\"furniture\" width=\"521\" height=\"399\"></a> <a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/furniture2.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-671\">\r\n</a></span></p>', 'Mensa Furniture', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '669-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-23 09:15:21', '2017-06-23 09:15:21', '', 669, 'http://localhost/project_week/2017/06/23/669-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(780, 1, '2017-06-23 09:15:49', '2017-06-23 09:15:49', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">5 team members of water project: Bruno, Kylie, Pietro, Naim and Tamar decided to compose a project week connected to the problem of water consumption not only in the school itself but in the local community: Maastricht. After several meetings we agreed on 2 major activities we wanted to undertake in this small period of time. First two days we spend researching and executing several trials to make homemade toothpaste, together with a small advertisement.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/kiitan.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-665\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-665\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/kiitan.png\" alt=\"kiitan\" width=\"615\" height=\"452\"></a>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Regular toothpastes from shop contain a large amount of plastic and chemicals in it, moreover the production of such a good creates a lot of plastic waste since it’s tube can not be reused. Therefore our homemade toothpaste would be healthier for teeth and more sustainable, since we plan to reuse the glass jars. The last two days we went to the city and interviewed people asking them if they were aware about their water consumption habits. As we could see by the people’s reactions during the interviews, a lot of people are still not aware of their water footprint i.e. how much water they use in their daily lives. This causes them to over consume water while around billion people lack access to clean water. It was a surprise even for us to come across a fact that by 2025, two-thirds of the world’s population is expected to be facing water shortages.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/waterproject.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-666\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-666\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/waterproject.png\" alt=\"waterproject\" width=\"573\" height=\"376\"></a>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We are ready to set up a toothpaste enterprise during next year that can reduce water consumption, and we have footage for a documentary that we are going to show to school when we’re done cutting important parts and editing. We also think the documentary will have room outside the school. With this, we are contributing towards a more sustainable future which is part of the UWC values.\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/waterproject1.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-667\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-667\" src=\"http://uwcmaastrichtimpact.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/waterproject1.png\" alt=\"waterproject1\" width=\"872\" height=\"391\"></a>', 'The Water Project', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '664-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-23 09:15:49', '2017-06-23 09:15:49', '', 664, 'http://localhost/project_week/2017/06/23/664-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
